	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Is it possible to quickly replace the battery in a GAR without wiping out the code stored in RAM or will the RAM instantly flush once the charge is lost.  I have a functioning cart and would like to put in a fresh battery.
<br />
<br />Or is there a procedure for maintaining a constant current while switching out the battery.
<br />
<br />If not I'll probably just buy a CopyNes and utilize the GAR fix button.  I assume this function dumps the code back into the carts RAM once a fresh battery has been installed.  I went to Kevtris's site but didn't see a descripton of the GAR fix details.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
